        "title": "refactor: prune unused iOS code",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Prunes unused internal iOS helpers, constants, and view surfaces.\r\n- Removes tests that only covered the deleted helper surfaces.\r\n- Keeps persisted Codable shapes and active decode paths intact.\r\n- The best part is that it is all source controlled - we can always bring it back\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- `xcodebuild test -project apps/ios/OpenClaw.xcodeproj -scheme OpenClawLogicTests -configuration Debug -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro,OS=26.5' CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO` -> `TEST SUCCEEDED`\r\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` -> clean, no accepted/actionable findings\r\n- Rebased on fresh `origin/main` before push (`50c20682`)\r\n\r\n## Build Note\r\n\r\nA full `OpenClaw` app build with Xcode 27 beta is blocked on current `main` by the deprecated WatchKit product type `com.apple.product-type.watchkit2-extension`. For build-only confirmation, I temporarily removed the generated watch targets, regenerated the Xcode project, and verified `xcodebuild build -scheme OpenClaw -destination 'generic/platform=iOS' CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO` -> `BUILD SUCCEEDED`; that temporary watch-target removal was reverted before this PR.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n- Behavior or issue addressed: unused iOS code and tests were removed without changing persisted decode paths.\r\n- Real environment tested: local macOS with Xcode 26.5 and Xcode 27 beta installed, running the real `apps/ios/OpenClaw.xcodeproj`.\r\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: OpenClawLogicTests command above; autoreview command above; generic iOS device build with temporary main-watch workaround described above.\r\n- Evidence after fix: terminal capture from the real local Xcode build/test commands:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n$ DEVELOPER_DIR=/Applications/Xcode-26.5.0.app/Contents/Developer xcodebuild test \\\r\n  -project apps/ios/OpenClaw.xcodeproj \\\r\n  -scheme OpenClawLogicTests \\\r\n  -configuration Debug \\\r\n  -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro,OS=26.5' \\\r\n  CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO\r\n1365:** TEST SUCCEEDED **\r\n\r\n$ .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main\r\nautoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\r\noverall: patch is correct (0.84)\r\n\r\n$ xcodebuild build \\\r\n  -project apps/ios/OpenClaw.xcodeproj \\\r\n  -scheme OpenClaw \\\r\n  -configuration Debug \\\r\n  -destination 'generic/platform=iOS' \\\r\n  CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO\r\n5901:** BUILD SUCCEEDED **\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Observed result after fix: active iOS logic tests pass, reviewer found no actionable issues, and the generic iOS device app build passes when the existing `main` WatchKit target blocker is temporarily disabled and then reverted.\r\n- What was not tested: current-branch full `OpenClaw` app build with watch targets intact, because Xcode 27 beta rejects the deprecated WatchKit extension from `main` before compiling this patch.\r\n",
